  <brief_title>Trial to Evaluate Erectile Function, Fertility and Sperm Count in Male Cyclists Compared to Age Matched Controls</brief_title>
  <official_title>Prospective Controlled Trial to Evaluate Erectile Function, Fertility and Sperm Count in Male Cyclists Compared to Age Matched Controls</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Sheba Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Sheba Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bicycle riding is associated with related diverse urogenital symptoms ranging from genital
      numbness to erectile dysfunction (ED). Very little is known about the quality of sperm in
      cyclists and whether a connection exists between erectile dysfunction and azoospermia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
